In field hockey, she was a four-year Captain and First Team All-State goalie. In ice hockey, she was a team captain her junior and senior year and made the US Development Team following her sophomore season. In lacrosse, Field was a four-year starting goalie and a team captain her junior and senior seasons. She led her squad to two straight State Championship titles in 2009 and 2010. Field was the top high school goalie in the state of New Hampshire all four years at Hollis-Brookline. She was fetted with All-Conference and All-State honors for four straight seasons. Her junior and senior year she earned All-American honors. Field also played on the prestigious Upper New England Team in 2009 and 2010.
